  "prompt": "What norms and standards does a design institute follow?",
  "response": "Design institutes typically follow various norms and standards depending on their specific field and region. Here are some common standards and norms across different design disciplines:\n\n1. General Design Standards:\n- ISO 9001 Quality Management\n- International design guidelines\n- Ergonomic standards\n- Accessibility requirements\n- Safety regulations\n\n2. Industrial Design Standards:\n- ASTM International design standards\n- Manufacturing specifications\n- Material safety standards\n- Product performance criteria\n\n3. Architectural Design Standards:\n- Building codes\n- Zoning regulations\n- Construction standards\n- Energy efficiency requirements\n- Structural safety norms\n\n4. Graphic Design Standards:\n- Color management standards\n- Digital file formatting guidelines\n- Typography best practices\n- Branding consistency protocols\n\n5. User Experience (UX) Design Standards:\n- Web accessibility guidelines (WCAG)\n- Interaction design principles\n- User interface design standards\n- Digital platform compatibility norms\n\n6. Environmental Design Standards:\n- Sustainability certifications\n- Green building standards\n- Environmental impact assessment guidelines\n\n7. Professional Ethics and Practices:\n- Professional conduct codes\n- Intellectual property guidelines\n- Client confidentiality standards\n\nThese standards ensure quality, safety, consistency, and professional excellence across design disciplines.",
